The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Mumbai, Jan. 15 (PTI): The Shiv Sena today said it was not opposed to Sachin Tendulkar featuring in the Save Water campaign of the Brihanmumbai Municipal Corporation, but was against the script of the short film.          
	Sachin says he has shifted from taking a shower to using a bucketful of water for bathing. How would a common Mumbaikar understand this as only a few of them take a shower? the Senas leader in the civic body, Sunil Prabhu, said.                  
	 Amritsar: A clash between two smuggler gangs saw bullets flying outside an Amritsar court on Friday. One gang member, identified as Raju, suffered head injury in the shootout that started when a member of the Boxer gang, called Jagtar, was being brought to the court. Members of the rival Ankur Lakhari gang were waiting in an SUV near the court and fired at Jagtar. In retaliation, Boxer gang members and the police opened fire.                   
	 Moga (PTI): The pistol of a senior police officer guarding the Punjab chief minister has been stolen. Deputy superintendent of police Ram Parkash said he had kept the pistol and 30 cartridges in a bag in his office vehicle on Thursday. The bag has gone missing.                  
	 Kokrajhar: Two bike-borne persons hurled a grenade in Udalguri town in Lower Assam, killing a member of the Asom Jatiyatabadi Yuba Chhatra Parishad. The blast that killed Gagan Das injured 10 others.                   
	 Jammu (PTI): Two armymen, including an officer, were killed in a fire that broke out at a training camp in Udhampur district of Jammu and Kashmir on Friday morning. The dead were identified as Lieutenant Girish Tiwari and havildar Vinod Kumar.                  
	 Panaji (PTI): A case of rash driving has been registered against the son of a Goa inspector-general of police. Siddharth had rammed father K.D. Singhs official car into an electricity pole while returning from a pub on Friday. Singh said his son had taken the car without informing him.                                                                                                                                              
